que et individuelle, sont destinés à des parties contractuelles désocialisées, voire réifiées.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLAW / Civil Rights.2bisacsh  acontrat juridique.  acontrat.  adroit civil.  athéorie contractuelle.1 aDufour, Pascale, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFokou, Éric, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9782766301942?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782766301942423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782766301942/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles